         <div type="transcription">
            <p>
<lb corresp="#a1"/></p>
            <lg type="poem" met="frg:M12" subtype="hom">
               <lg n="1" type="strophe">
                  <l n="a"><w>salpeṃ</w><w>piś</w><w>cmela</w><caesura ana="frg:cs-s"/><w>añityātṣe</w><caesura ana="frg:cs-w"/><w>puwarsa</w><pc>•</pc></l>
                  <l n="b"><w>koyn</w><w>kakāyaṣ</w><w>po</w><caesura ana="frg:cs-s"/><w>kaṣāntaṣṣi</w><caesura ana="frg:cs-w"/><w>kāri</w><w>po</w><pc>•</pc></l>
                  <l n="c"><w>tāṣṭär</w><w>pelaikne</w><caesura ana="frg:cs-s"/><w>śaulanmasa</w><caesura ana="frg:cs-w"/><w>käryau</w><w>se</w><pc>•</pc></l>
                  <l n="d"><w>tneka</w><w>preksaume</w><caesura ana="frg:cs-s"/><w>kā</w><w>snai</w><w>meṃtsi</w><caesura ana="frg:cs-w"/><w>kläṃtsañcer</w></l>
               </lg>
            </lg>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Those of the five-births burn in the fire of inconstancy, all having opened their mouths, all are pits of <hi>kapānta</hi>, he establishes the law and bought [it] with lives, here indeed I ask you, "how do you sleep without a care?"</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="philcomment">metre 4x12, rythm 5/7</note></p>
         </div>
